# OCaml Stdlib Preferences

Prefer module-qualified functions over legacy top-level aliases:

- `Int.of_string` instead of `int_of_string`
- `Int.of_string_opt` instead of `int_of_string_opt`
- `Int.to_string` instead of `string_of_int`
- `Float.of_string` instead of `float_of_string`
- `Float.of_string_opt` instead of `float_of_string_opt`
- `Float.to_string` instead of `string_of_float`

Unless specified, do not use `failwith`, neither `assert(false)`.

# Pattern Matching Style

Prefer type annotation on the matched value over module-qualified constructors:

```ocaml
(* ✅ Preferred *)
match (value : Module.t) with
| Constructor_1 -> ...
| Constructor_2 -> ...

(* ❌ Avoid *)
match value with
| Module.Constructor_1 -> ...
| Module.Constructor_2 -> ...
```
